						<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
					</div>
					<div id="contentSub"><div id="mw-content-subtitle"><span class="mw-redirectedfrom">(Redirected from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Christian_angelology&amp;redirect=no" class="mw-redirect" title="Christian angelology">Christian angelology</a>)</span></div></div>
					
					
					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><p class="mw-empty-elt">
</p>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg/310px-Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg" decoding="async" width="310" height="188" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg/465px-Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg/620px-Francesco_Botticini_-_The_Assumption_of_the_Virgin.jpg 2x" data-file-width="6000" data-file-height="3643" /></a><figcaption>The <i><a href="/wiki/Assumption_of_the_Virgin_(Botticini)" title="Assumption of the Virgin (Botticini)">Assumption of the Virgin</a></i> by <a href="/wiki/Francesco_Botticini" title="Francesco Botticini">Francesco Botticini</a> (1475–1476) at the National Gallery London, shows three <a href="/wiki/Hierarchy_of_angels" title="Hierarchy of angels">hierarchies</a> and nine orders of angels, each with different characteristics.</figcaption></figure>
<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Nine_orders_of_angels.jpeg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e2/Nine_orders_of_angels.jpeg/310px-Nine_orders_of_angels.jpeg" decoding="async" width="310" height="471" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e2/Nine_orders_of_angels.jpeg 1.5x" data-file-width="428" data-file-height="650" /></a><figcaption>Eastern <a href="/wiki/Icon" title="Icon">icon</a> of nine orders of angels</figcaption></figure>
